The paper discusses the application of Knowledge Graphs (KGs) to various tasks, including natural language processing and entity linking, which are typically covered under the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.CL. The paper proposes a new open-world Knowledge Graph Completion (KGC) task, which involves adding new entities to the KG, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.DB and cs.IR. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB, and cs.CL.
